Topic 1: Algorithm Analysis

            This topic may sound basic, but Google interviewers use it to judge your engineering maturity.  
            Many candidates can write code.
            Few candidates can explain why one solution is better than another.
            That's exactly what algorithm analysis teaches.
====================================================================================================================================================================================
What is an Algorithm?

                    An algorithm is simply a sequence of steps that solves a problem.

        Example:
        
                    Finding a name inside a phonebook.
                    
                    Finding a file on disk.
                    
                    Searching Google.
                    
                    Routing a packet.
                    
                    Calculating GPS directions.
                    
                    Everything is an algorithm.

The real question is:

                      How efficient is it?

That is what complexity analysis answers.

====================================================================================================================================================================================
Why Complexity Matters:

            Imagine Google receives:     1 billion requests/day
                            
            Suppose one algorithm takes:  100 ms
                            
            Another takes:      10 ms
                            
            Difference?:     90 ms
                            
            Seems small.!!!!!
                            
            Now multiply:      90 ms × 1,000,000,000
                            
                That's 90 million seconds of extra CPU time.
                            
At Google's scale, an algorithm that's only slightly more efficient can save enormous compute resources.

That's why interviewers care about complexity—     they want engineers who can reason about efficiency at scale.

