Time Complexity

              Time complexity measures:     How does the running time grow as the input size grows?

                Notice:  We don't measure
                
                          seconds
                          milliseconds
                          CPU speed
                
                Instead we measure
                
                            Growth
                
                Example
                
                          Suppose
                          
                          n = number of elements
                          
                          Algorithm A
                
                             for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                                        System.out.println(i);
                                    }
                
                How many times does the loop execute?  :     n
                                    
                                    Therefore   :     Time = n
                                    
                                    We write    :    O(n)


            Example 2
            
                        Nested loop
                        
                                    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                                    
                                        for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                                    
                                        }
                                    
                                    }
                                    
                        Outer loop  :n
                                    
                        Inner loop  : n
                                    
                         Total:  n*n =  O(n²)

            Example 3

                        Binary Search
                        
                                    Every iteration:   Half the search space.
                                    
