Interview Question  : Google interviewer:     Why is Binary Search O(log n)?
                        
Bad answer:   Because everyone says so.
                        
Good answer:  Every iteration eliminates half of the remaining search space.
                        
            After k iterations:                        
                        n / 2^k = 1
                        
            Solving for k:                        
                        2^k = n                        
                        k = log₂ n                        
            Therefore,                        
                        Time Complexity = O(log n) 

This mathematical reasoning is what interviewers appreciate.
